   VERSION=( "2.09" "1.33" )
 ATTRIBUTE="x11"
  CATEGORY="utility"
    SOURCE="gpsdrive-$VERSION"
       URL="http://www.kraftvoll.at/software"
  HOMEPAGE="http://www.kraftvoll.at/software/index.shtml"
       REQ="gtk+ pcre"
 FRESHMEAT="gpsdrive"
  ESTIMATE="98"
     SHORT="GPS software for Linux"
LONG="
GpsDrive is a car (bike, ship, plane) navigation system. 
GpsDrive displays your position provided from your NMEA 
capable GPS receiver on a zoomable map, the map file is
autoselected depending of the position and prefered scale.
Speech output is supported if the \"festival\" software is 
running. The maps are autoselected for best resolution 
depending of your position and can be downloaded from 
Internet. All Garmin GPS reveiver with a serial output 
should be usable, also other GPS receiver which supports 
NMEA protocol.
"
